<HEADLINE>
CLA UNVEILS 'HAPPINESS' PROGRAM FOR WAGE EARNERS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Feb. 12 (CNA) 02/12/07  21:44:12 (By Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
The Council of Labor Affairs (CLA) has come up with a NT$10
billion (US$303 million) program to provide new welfare services
for the country's 8 million wage earners, CLA officials said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the new "Happiness" plan, the CLA will earmark
NT$3.7 billion for employment boosting programs; NT$2.7 billion
for projects to subsidize childbirth, child care and education,
including increasing childbirth subsidy from one month's salary
to three months'; NT$2 billion for a plan to provide subsidies
for workers to purchase residential units; and NT$1 billion for
projects aimed at helping laborers improve their professional
skills.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the CLA also plans to improve labor insurance
benefits, including relaxing restrictions on payments to laborers
who fall ill or are wounded on the job, the officials said.
</P>
